Intuition
so our method is we will passy the array only once and we will sort it , in 1 pass , for that we will need 3 pointers , low to store value of zeroes , high to score value of 2s and , mid to check where we are currently and compare, so we send all the zeros towards low , and all the 2 towards high and remain 1 at their place .

Approach
step 1 , set low = 0 and mid = 0 , high = n-1
step 2 ,loop condition is we traverse until mid crosses high
step 3 , if nums[mid] == 2 we swap it with high and decrease high
step 4 if nums[mid] == 0 we swap mid with low and increase low and mid
step 5 if nums[mid] == 1 , we just increase mid

Complexity
Time complexity:
O(n)

Space complexity:
O(1)

Code
class Solution:
    def sortColors(self, nums: List[int]) -> None:
        """
        Do not return anything, modify nums in-place instead.
        """
        n = len(nums)
        low = 0
        mid = 0 
        high = n - 1

        while mid <= high :
            if nums[mid] == 2:
                nums[mid] , nums[high] = nums[high] , nums[mid]
                high -= 1
            elif nums[mid] == 0:
                nums[mid] , nums[low] = nums[low] ,nums[mid]
                low += 1
                mid += 1
            else: #nums[mid] == 1
                mid += 1
